$ Oracle: SQL work areas

The *SQL work areas* are part of the → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance/PGA and are used for operations that require non-trivial amounts of memory, such as
  • sorting data
  • grouping data into hash buckets

sa:
  The → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/init-parameters/workarea_size_policy[init parameter `workarea_size_policy`].
